SIMPLE: slaver
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slaver
<hw>Slav"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A vessel
engaged in the slave trade; a slave ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person engaged in the purchase and sale of slaves;
a slave merchant, or slave trader.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>slaver's</qex> hand was on the latch,⟦br⟧
He seemed in haste to go.</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slaver</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slaver
<hw>Slav"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Slavered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Slavering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>slafra</ets>. See <er>Slabber</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
suffer spittle, etc., to run from the mouth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be besmeared with saliva.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slaver</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Slaver
<hw>Slav"er</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To smear with saliva issuing
from the mouth; to defile with drivel; to slabber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slaver</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Slaver
<hw>Slav"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Saliva driveling from the
mouth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of all mad creatures, if the learned are right,⟦br⟧
It is the <qex>slaver</qex> kills, and not the bite.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slaverer</ent>⟦br⟧
